// There is two type of data type in java primitive and Non-primitive Data Type.
// Primitive data types are ( byte,int,float,long,char,double,bool,short)
// byte can hold values from -128 to 127 number, int store decimal number , char store single characters ,bool store true and false , long store large int number , float store fractional numbers with 6-7 total digits , double store fractional numbers with 15 digits , short store int numbers from -32,768 to 32,767.
// Non-primitive data types in Java are not predefined They are created by the programmer Examples of non-primitive types include strings, arrays, and classes

public class Class_2{
    public static void main(String[] args){

// this is how we write variable in java ( DataType VariableName = value )
// variable name must not be digits , name is case sensitive , it should not be key words like (void,static.. etc), space is not allowed in name , can contain alphabets , $ character , _ Character and digits if others conditions are met example: ( number_1, star$ )
// java is statically typed -> variable must be declared before use
// 1 byte = 8 bit.The byte values of data types( byte takes/size 1 bytes,short takes 2 bytes,int takes 4 bytes,float takes 4 bytes,long takes 8 bytes,double takes 8 bytes,char takes 2 bytes,bool size is depends on jvm(means machine) )
// to calculate the value range of data types ( -2^8n to 2^8n-1 ) it is the formula. example: ( for byte data type -2^8*1 / 2 to 2^8*1 / 2 -1 = - 2^8 /2 to 2^8/2 -1 = -128 to 127 ) [only char data type value range start from 0 to 2^8n -1 & bool data type value range is only true or false]
